sec.p:
The Mordecai et al. (2013) model measured transmission using R0, the number of secondary infections expected when an infected individual enters a fully susceptible population. The model is an extension of the classic Kermack–McKendrick model, and R0 is given by:
\documentclass{aastex}\usepackage{amsbsy}\usepackage{amsfonts}\usepackage{amssymb}\usepackage{bm}\usepackage{mathrsfs}\usepackage{pifont}\usepackage{stmaryrd}\usepackage{textcomp}\usepackage{portland, xspace}\usepackage{amsmath, amsxtra}\pagestyle{empty}\DeclareMathSizes{10}{9}{7}{6}\begin{document}
\begin{align*}R_0 = \sqrt { \frac { M }  { Nr } \frac { a^2 bc \ exp ( - \mu / PDR ) }  { \mu } } \end{align*}
\end{document}
